dev/plans/runs/B1-multithread-wiring-20260504T020828Z.log:4061:{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01PXaJqBRTMSyjp29K1qjRaW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Skip `agent-verify.sh` — source matches baseline post-revert (nothing changed to verify). Output written; source clean.\n\n## Final result — B.1 REVERT\n\n- **Decision**: REVERT (numeric rule: concurrent_median 120.6 ms > 115 ms)\n- **Commit SHA**: none\n- **Worktree**: `/tmp/fdb-pack5-B1-multithread-wiring-20260504T020828Z`\n- **Output JSON**: `dev/plan/runs/B1-multithread-wiring-output.json` (untracked; orchestrator harvests)\n\n### Key numbers (N=5, all release builds)\n\n| metric            | A.1 baseline | B.1 after | delta    |\n|-------------------|--------------|-----------|----------|\n| sequential median | 182 ms       | 184.0 ms  | +1.10%   |\n| concurrent median | 115 ms       | 120.6 ms  | +4.87%   |\n| speedup median    | 1.58×        | 1.526×    | -3.42%   |\n| stddev concurrent | 4.0 ms       | 2.98 ms   | —        |\n\n### Critical signal — config_rc=0 confirmed\n\n`init_sqlite_runtime()` wired at `open_locked` head BEFORE `register_sqlite_vec_extension` and any `Connection::open`. Captured rcs: shutdown=0, config=0 (SQLITE_OK), initialize=0. New `pub fn sqlite_runtime_config_rc() -> Option<i32>` accessor + 2-test file (`tests/multithread_wiring.rs`) verified `Some(0)` post-open and idempotency across reopens. Both tests passed before revert.\n\nThis is the **§5 differentiator**: §5 returned 21 (SQLITE_MISUSE) silently. B.1 returned 0 — wiring is provably correct. Yet AC-020 ratio is flat → hypothesis \"runtime threading-mode flag relieves bottleneck\" is **falsified**.\n\n### data_for_pivot — APPLIED-BUT-DIDN'T-HELP\n\nRuntime CONFIG_MULTITHREAD downgrade does not touch the contended primitives observed in A.1 (`__aarch64_swp4_rel`, `__aarch64_cas4_acq`, `___pthread_mutex_lock`). Two surviving hypotheses:\n- **C.1** (compile-time `SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2` / `SQLITE_NO_MUTEX` rebuild) — directly disables per-conn mutex; smaller-radius test.\n- **D.1** (architectural — per-conn lookaside or alt reader topology) — kill mutex track if C.1 also flat.\n\n### next_phase_recommendation: **C1**\n\n### Tests passing pre-revert\nmultithread_wiring (2/2), AC-017 green, AC-018 green, lifecycle_reliability (4/4), vector_contracts (7/7), projection_runtime (12/12), op_store (7/7), error_taxonomy (12/12), instrumentation_methods (5/5), cursor_read_after_write (1/1), search_result_shape (2/2), property_template (1/1), lib (1/1). Pre-existing A.0 compile errors in tests/{compatibility,cursors,lifecycle_observability}.rs unchanged.\n\n### git_status_clean_after_revert: true\n(Only untracked `dev/plan/runs/B1-multithread-wiring-output.json`; production source identical to baseline `fc3dda3`.)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":656,"cache_read_input_tokens":85490,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":656},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8e03970-0bb0-4f28-945f-ef09a4c5917b","uuid":"cd90015e-c752-41bd-afde-3ad12c6668f0"}
