dev/plans/runs/C1-threadsafe2-rebuild-20260504T022727Z.log:2721:{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AbUTehbmo2y6tKw1wH8KS8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"agent-verify.sh passed with exit 0. That means lint, typecheck, and tests all pass. \n\nNow let me revert the code changes since the decision is REVERT:\n1. Delete `.cargo/config.toml`\n2. Revert `Cargo.toml` comment\n3. Delete `tests/compile_options.rs`\n\nBut wait - should I keep the compile_options.rs test? The TDD instruction says I added a failing test first. Now that it passes (with the build flag), but we're REVERTing, should I keep the test file? If I keep it, it will FAIL after removing the build flag (since THREADSAFE would be 1 again).\n \nActually, the correct TDD behavior on REVERT is to revert the test too, since it's only valid for the C.1 implementation. Without the build flag, the test would fail because THREADSAFE defaults back to 1. So I need to remove all three changes: the config file, the Cargo.toml comment, and the test file. I'll preserve the evidence in the runs directory and write the output JSON, then commit everything along with any plan doc updates. Let me also check the binary size from the B.1 output JSON for baseline comparison.\n\nLooking at the B.1 output, there's no binary_size_release_bytes field, but the C.1 template requires it. I'll just note the rlib size since I don't have a pre-C.1 baseline to compare against. For the documentation question, I shouldn't update dev/interfaces/rust.md with the build flag instructions since I'm reverting that change—the interface file would become stale immediately. Per the guidelines about staleness, I'll skip the documentation update for the REVERT path.\n\nNow I'll execute the revert, generate the output JSON, and commit the evidence.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":125,"cache_read_input_tokens":71132,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":125},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8996a1e6-f0cf-41f6-bd76-ad56a5a9b42e","uuid":"a3d95aa9-1cbd-4fc2-bdcf-f3610ebb25ba"}
