ize\": 0,\n43\t    \"page_size\": 4096,\n44\t    \"synchronous\": 2\n45\t  },\n46\t  \"explain_query_plan\": [\n47\t    {\n48\t      \"statement\": \"vec0_match\",\n49\t      \"plan_summary\": \"SCAN vector_default VIRTUAL TABLE INDEX 0:3{___}___; USE TEMP B-TREE FOR ORDER BY\",\n50\t      \"regression\": false,\n51\t      \"notes\": \"vec0 virtual table SCAN with INDEX is expected; internal ANN index used transparently; TEMP B-TREE ORDER BY normal for vec0\"\n52\t    },\n53\t    {\n54\t      \"statement\": \"canonical_lookup\",\n55\t      \"plan_summary\": \"SCAN canonical_nodes\",\n56\t      \"regression\": false,\n57\t      \"notes\": \"Real-table full scan for WHERE write_cursor = ?1 LIMIT 1. No index on write_cursor. Latent scale concern (O(n) with node count). Not a planner regression — index never created. Flag for structural review.\"\n58\t    },\n59\t    {\n60\t      \"statement\": \"soft_fallback_probe\",\n61\t      \"plan_summary\": \"SCAN search_index VIRTUAL TABLE INDEX 0:M3; SEARCH _fathomdb_vector_kinds USING COVERING INDEX; SEARCH _fathomdb_projection_terminal USING INTEGER PRIMARY KEY LEFT-JOIN\",\n62\t      \"regression\": false,\n63\t      \"notes\": \"FTS5 MATCH SCAN expected; both joins use indexed paths\"\n64\t    },\n65\t    {\n66\t      \"statement\": \"fts_match\",\n67\t      \"plan_summary\": \"SCAN search_index VIRTUAL TABLE INDEX 0:M3; USE TEMP B-TREE FOR ORDER BY\",\n68\t      \"regression\": false,\n69\t      \"notes\": \"FTS5 MATCH SCAN expected; TEMP B-TREE for ORDER BY write_cursor normal for FTS5\"\n70\t    }\n71\t  ],\n72\t  \"explain_regression_observed\": false,\n73\t  \"consistency_check_vs_a1_a2\": \"agree: A.2 identified mutex_atomic as dominant (5.73× growth). THREADSAFE=1 + MUTEX_PTHREADS confirms SQLite uses pthreads mutexes internally. With 8 threads and 8 readers in ReaderPool, the pool Mutex itself is a contention point — all threads compete to borrow/release via Mutex<Vec<Connection>>. The proxy counter shows search_us_per_query=542µs concurrent with embedder~0µs, meaning borrow+read dominates. This is consistent with A.2 mutex_atomic signal. strace futex count unavailable but THREADSAFE=1 pthreads path is confirmed.\",\n74\t  \"data_for_pivot\": \"THREADSAFE=1 (MUTEX_PTHREADS) confirmed. A.2 mutex_atomic 5.73× growth + THREADSAFE=1 together point clearly at MULTITHREAD (THREADSAFE=2) upgrade as the targeted intervention: SQLite SERIALIZED mode uses a global recursive mutex per connection; switching to MULTITHREAD removes that per-connection serialization. ReaderPool has 8 connections and 8 threads — pool size is not the bottleneck, but the Mutex<Vec<Connection>> in ReaderPool::borrow/release adds Rust-side contention on top of SQLite's own per-connection mutex. B.1 should address both layers. The canonical_lookup full-scan (no index on write_cursor) is a secondary latency contributor that will grow with data volume — worth a follow-up but not the primary bottleneck at current fixture size.\",\n75\t  \"unexpected_observations\": \"1) canonical_nodes has no index on write_cursor — a full table scan for each vec0 match result. Current fixture is 4 rows so invisible in perf, but this will degrade at scale. 2) DEFAULT_MMAP_SIZE=0 — no memory-mapped I/O configured; all reads go through the SQLite page cache (DEFAULT_CACHE_SIZE=-2000, ~8MB per connection × 9 connections = ~72MB total potential cache). 3) DEFAULT_SYNCHRONOUS=2 (FULL) — no WAL-specific reduction; writes are sync-heavy but reads are unaffected. 4) reader_pragmas show mmap_size=0 confirming no mmap on readers. 5) embedder_us=23µs total across 1600 queries (0µs/query) — embedder is entirely off the critical path for RoutedEmbedder; real production embedder latency would change this picture significantly.\",\n76\t  \"evidence_dir\": \"dev/plan/runs/A3-evidence/\",\n77\t  \"log_path\": \"dev/plan/runs/A3-secondary-diagnostics-output.json\",\n78\t  \"next_phase_recommendation\": \"Feeds A4 decision: THREADSAFE=1 confirmed (baseline for B.1 MULTITHREAD=2 target). mutex_atomic A.2 verdict corroborated by MUTEX_PTHREADS compile option. strace unavailable but not blocking — A.2 flamegraph evidence is sufficient. A.4 can proceed with: THREADSAFE=1 baseline, mutex_atomic dominant, canonical_lookup missing-index as secondary observation. B.1 should target sqlite3_config(SQLITE_CONFIG_MULTITHREAD) + potentially add write_cursor index on canonical_nodes.\"\n79\t}\n80\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38adc285-4437-4bbf-a855-0849e65f1132","uuid":"d8579e5c-1fd4-41f8-9207-92d88075280a","timestamp":"2026-05-04T02:49:23.105Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-pack5-E1-prepare-cached-readers-20260504T024906Z/dev/plan/runs/A3-secondary-diagnostics-output.json","content":"{\n  \"phase\": \"A3\",\n  \"decision\": \"PARTIAL\",\n  \"strace_top_10_syscalls\": [],\n  \"strace_summary\": {\n    \"total_syscalls\": null,\n    \"total_wall_s\": null,\n    \"futex_share_pct\": null,\n    \"io_share_pct\": null,\n    \"skip_reason\": \"strace not installed, no sudo access; see A3-evidence/strace-skipped.md\"\n  },\n  \"counters\": {\n    \"reader_borrow_ms_total\": null,\n    \"reader_borrow_ms_per_query\": null,\n    \"embedder_us_total\": 23,\n    \"embedder_us_per_query\": 0,\n    \"search_us_total\": 867569,\n    \"search_us_per_query\": 542,\n    \"proxy_borrow_plus_read_us_total\": 867546,\n    \"proxy_borrow_plus_read_us_per_query\": 542,\n    \"prepares_per_search\": 4,\n    \"queries_total\": 1600\n  },\n  \"counters_collection_status\": \"partial:borrow_wait and read_search_in_tx split require production hooks; search_us covers both; embed is RoutedEmbedder (~0 us), so proxy_borrow_plus_read_us ≈ search_us\",\n  \"threadsafe\": 1,\n  \"compile_options\": {\n    \"threadsafe\": \"THREADSAFE=1\",\n    \"memsys\": \"\",\n    \"mutex\": \"MUTEX_PTHREADS\",\n    \"default_pagesize\": \"DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE=4096\",\n    \"default_cache_size\": \"DEFAULT_CACHE_SIZE=-2000\",\n