dev/plans/runs/E1-prepare-cached-readers-20260504T024906Z.log:5483:{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TghTw8fUnPZPACq8vLoMC9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `execute_for_test` is `#[cfg(debug_assertions)]` gated, but we're running in `--release` mode which disables `debug_assertions`. This seems to be a pre-existing issue with the test suite, not something I introduced.\n\nLet me verify this by checking whether this error also occurs on the base branch (before my changes). Actually I can't check the base branch easily. Let me check if this is a pre-existing issue by checking the git log.\n\nWait, the mandate says:\n> ```bash\n\n\n> cargo test -p fathomdb-engine --release \\\n>     --test prepare_cached_readers\n> cargo test -p fathomdb-engine --release\n> ```\n\nSo `cargo test -p fathomdb-engine --release` is in the verification commands. If it was failing before my changes on the base, that's a pre-existing issue. Looking at the error more closely, `execute_for_test` is gated with `#[cfg(debug_assertions)]` in lib.rs, which means in `--release` mode where debug assertions are off by default, the method simply doesn't exist.\n\nThe test file `lifecycle_observability.rs` is calling this method unconditionally, so either this is a pre-existing issue or tests aren't normally run in release mode. Let me check how the agent-verify.sh script actually runs the tests.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":715,"cache_read_input_tokens":100074,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":715},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38adc285-4437-4bbf-a855-0849e65f1132","uuid":"cbcc3380-1a99-414b-a697-33b8dd6a755a"}
