dev/plans/runs/F0-review-20260504T121732Z.md:1308:dev/plans/runs/A3-secondary-diagnostics-output.json:73: "consistency_check_vs_a1_a2": "agree: A.2 identified mutex_atomic as dominant (5.73× growth). THREADSAFE=1 + MUTEX_PTHREADS confirms SQLite uses pthreads mutexes internally. With 8 threads and 8 readers in ReaderPool, the pool Mutex itself is a contention point — all threads compete to borrow/release via Mutex<Vec<Connection>>. The proxy counter shows search_us_per_query=542µs concurrent with embedder~0µs, meaning borrow+read dominates. This is consistent with A.2 mutex_atomic signal. strace futex count unavailable but THREADSAFE=1 pthreads path is confirmed.",
