     9	
    10	# 12-TX Parity Matrix
    11	
    12	Snapshot taken at slice start of Phase 12-TX (TS → Python parity audit).
    13	Per `dev/design/bindings.md` § 1, the parity claim is "same five-verb
    14	canonical set + same error class taxonomy + same data shapes in
    15	language-idiomatic spelling". Cross-language idiom differences
    16	(`camelCase` vs `snake_case`; positional vs kwarg; `Promise` vs sync;
    17	options-object vs keyword-arg) are **intentional per
    18	`dev/interfaces/typescript.md` and `dev/interfaces/python.md`** and are
    19	recorded here as `📋 divergence-by-design`, **not** as gaps.
    20	
    21	Legend:
    22	
    23	- ✅ **parity-OK** — both surfaces present; spec-compliant idiom differences acknowledged
    24	- ❌ **gap** — TS missing what Python has, or vice versa, where the locked interface spec implies parity
    25	- 📋 **divergence-by-design** — locked spec explicitly diverges
    26	
    27	## 1. Five-verb canonical surface (REQ-053; AC-057a)
    28	
    29	| Verb              | Python (`src/python/fathomdb/`)                                          | TypeScript (`src/ts/src/`)                                                                    | Status |
    30	| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------ |
    31	| `Engine.open`     | `Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config)` → `Engine`          | `Engine.open(path, options?)` → `Promise<Engine>`                                             | 📋 sync vs Promise; kwargs vs options-object; both per spec |
    32	| `engine.write`    | `engine.write(batch=None)` → `WriteReceipt` (sync)                       | `engine.write(batch=[])` → `Promise<WriteReceipt>`                                            | 📋 sync vs Promise per spec |
    33	| `engine.search`   | `engine.search(query)` → `SearchResult` (sync)                           | `engine.search(query)` → `Promise<SearchResult>`                                              | 📋 sync vs Promise per spec |
    34	| `engine.close`    | `engine.close()` → `None` (sync)                                         | `engine.close()` → `Promise<void>`                                                            | 📋 sync vs Promise per spec |
    35	| `admin.configure` | `admin.configure(engine, *, name, body)` → `WriteReceipt` (module-level) | `admin.configure(engine, { name, body })` → `Promise<WriteReceipt>` (object-literal namespace) | ✅    |
    36	
    37	## 2. Engine-attached instrumentation / control
    38	
    39	| Method                       | Python                                                                      | TypeScript                                                  | Status |
    40	| ---------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ------ |
    41	| `drain`                      | `engine.drain(*, timeout_s: float\|int = 0)` (sync)                          | `engine.drain(timeoutMs: number)` → `Promise<void>`         | 📋 timeout unit (seconds vs ms) + sync vs Promise per spec |
    42	| `counters`                   | `engine.counters()` → `CounterSnapshot` (empty dataclass; **drops** native fields) | `engine.counters()` → `CounterSnapshot` (6 fields populated) | ❌ **gap closed in 12-TX**: Python wrapper threw away the 6 fields the PyO3 layer already returns |
    43	| `set_profiling`              | `engine.set_profiling(*, enabled)`                                          | `engine.setProfiling(enabled)`                              | 📋 kwarg vs positional per spec |
    44	| `set_slow_threshold_ms`      | `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(*, value)`                                    | `engine.setSlowThresholdMs(value)`                          | 📋 kwarg vs positional per spec |
    45	| Subscriber attach            | `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None)`   | `engine.attachSubscriber(callback, { heartbeatIntervalMs? })` | 📋 logging.Logger vs callback per `interfaces/python.md` § 51 + `interfaces/typescript.md` § 54 (explicitly different host-adapter shapes) |
    46	
    47	## 3. Caller-visible data shapes
    48	
    49	| Shape                | Python field set                                                                                                              | TypeScript field set                                                                                                                                       | Status |
    50	| -------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------ |
    51	| `WriteReceipt`       | `cursor: int`                                                                                                                 | `cursor: number`                                                                                                                                           | ✅    |
    52	| `SoftFallback`       | `branch: Literal["vector","text"]`                                                                                            | `branch: "vector" \| "text"`                                                                                                                              | ✅    |
    53	| `SearchResult`       | `projection_cursor: int`, `soft_fallback: SoftFallback \| None`, `results: list[str]`                                          | `projectionCursor: number`, `softFallback: SoftFallback \| null`, `results: string[]`                                                                     | ✅ (casing) |
    54	| `CounterSnapshot`    | _(was: empty dataclass)_; **after 12-TX**: `queries`, `writes`, `write_rows`, `admin_ops`, `cache_hit`, `cache_miss` (all `int`) | `queries`, `writes`, `writeRows`, `adminOps`, `cacheHit`, `cacheMiss` (all `number`)                                                                       | ❌ → ✅ (gap closed; 6 fields added to Python dataclass + wired through `Engine.counters`) |
    55	| `EngineConfig`       | `embedder_pool_size`, `scheduler_runtime_threads`, `provenance_row_cap`, `embedder_call_timeout_ms`, `slow_threshold_ms` (all `int \| None`) | same five knobs, `Optional<number>`, camelCase                                                                                                            | ✅    |
    56	
    57	## 4. Error-class taxonomy (15+ leaves per `dev/design/errors.md`)
    58	
    59	Python defines a root `EngineError` plus 18 concrete leaves. TypeScript
    60	defines `FathomDbError` plus 18 concrete leaves. Both bindings expose
    61	1:1 the same leaf set:
    62	
    63	| Class                              | Python `errors.py` | TS `errors.ts` |
    64	| ---------------------------------- | ------------------ | -------------- |
    65	| (root)                             | `EngineError`      | `FathomDbError`|
    66	| `StorageError`                     | ✅                | ✅            |
    67	| `ProjectionError`                  | ✅                | ✅            |
    68	| `VectorError`                      | ✅                | ✅            |
    69	| `EmbedderError`                    | ✅                | ✅            |
    70	| `EmbedderNotConfiguredError`       | ✅                | ✅            |
    71	| `KindNotVectorIndexedError`        | ✅                | ✅            |
    72	| `SchedulerError`                   | ✅                | ✅            |
    73	| `OpStoreError`                     | ✅                | ✅            |
    74	| `WriteValidationError`             | ✅                | ✅            |
    75	| `SchemaValidationError`            | ✅                | ✅            |
    76	| `OverloadedError`                  | ✅                | ✅            |
    77	| `ClosingError`                     | ✅                | ✅            |
    78	| `DatabaseLockedError`              | ✅ + `holder_pid` | ✅ + `holderPid` |
    79	| `CorruptionError`                  | ✅ + `kind` / `stage` / `recovery_hint_code` / `doc_anchor` | ✅ + `kind` / `stage` / `recoveryHintCode` / `docAnchor` |
    80	| `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`   | ✅                | ✅            |
    81	| `MigrationError`                   | ✅                | ✅            |
    82	| `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`    | ✅ + `stored_name` / `stored_revision` / `supplied_name` / `supplied_revision` | ✅ + camelCase counterparts |
    83	| `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`   | ✅ + `stored` / `supplied` | ✅ + `stored` / `supplied` |
    84	| Panic carrier (contract bug; not a `FathomDbError` subclass) | `pyo3_runtime.PanicException` (PyO3-owned, not `EngineError`) | `FathomDbPanicError` (TS-owned; not `FathomDbError`) | ✅ both deliberately outside the catch-all root |
    85	
    86	**Status: parity-OK after 12-TX.** No new TS leaves required.
