    10	# TypeScript Interface
    11	
    12	This file owns TypeScript-visible symbol spelling and export shape. Cross-
    13	binding parity remains owned by `design/bindings.md`.
    14	
    15	## Runtime surface
    16	
    17	The canonical runtime verbs available to TypeScript callers are:
    18	
    19	- `Engine.open(...)`
    20	- `engine.write(...)`
    21	- `engine.search(...)`
    22	- `engine.close()`
    23	- `admin.configure(...)`
    24	
    25	All runtime operations are Promise-returning on the TS surface.
    26	
    27	`Engine.open(...)` returns the engine handle plus the structured open report
    28	owned by `design/engine.md`.
    29	
    30	`Engine.open(path, options?)` accepts an options object with an `engineConfig`
    31	member carrying the engine-owned knobs from `design/engine.md` in camelCase:
    32	
    33	- `embedderPoolSize`
    34	- `schedulerRuntimeThreads`
    35	- `provenanceRowCap`
    36	- `embedderCallTimeoutMs`
    37	- `slowThresholdMs`
    38	
    39	If TypeScript exposes ThreadsafeFunction handoff-pool sizing, that option is a
    40	TS binding-runtime option beside `engineConfig`, not a canonical engine config
    41	field and not a Python parity obligation.
    42	
    43	## Engine-attached instrumentation / control
    44	
    45	These are public instance methods, not extra top-level SDK verbs:
    46	
    47	- `engine.drain(timeoutMs)`
    48	- `engine.counters()`
    49	- `engine.setProfiling(enabled)`
    50	- `engine.setSlowThresholdMs(value)`
    51	
    52	Subscriber attachment is provided by:
    53	
    54	- `engine.attachSubscriber(callback, { heartbeatIntervalMs? })`
    55	
    56	`callback` receives the stable `fathomdb` payload described in
    57	`design/bindings.md`.
    58	
    59	## Caller-visible data shapes
    60	
    61	- `WriteReceipt.cursor`
    62	- `SearchResult.projectionCursor`
    63	- `SearchResult.softFallback.branch`
    64	
    65	`softFallback.branch` uses the typed values owned by `design/retrieval.md`.
    66	
    67	## Errors
    68	
    69	TypeScript exposes one concrete leaf class per canonical row in
    70	`design/errors.md`.
    71	
    72	Leaf-class examples:
    73	
    74	- `DatabaseLockedError`
    75	- `CorruptionError`
    76	- `MigrationError`
    77	- `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`
    78	- `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`
    79	- `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`
    80	- `SchemaValidationError`
    81	- `OverloadedError`
    82	- `ClosingError`
    83	
    84	TypeScript exports one catch-all base class, `FathomDbError`, and every
    85	concrete leaf class in the `design/errors.md` matrix extends it. Open-time and
    86	runtime leaf classes remain distinct, but callers can catch `FathomDbError`
    87	for both.
    88	
    89	## Non-presence
    90	
    91	TypeScript does not expose recovery verbs or doctor-only flags. In particular,
    92	there is no SDK equivalent of `recover`, `checkIntegrity`, `quick`, `full`, or
    93	`roundTrip`. See `design/recovery.md`.

